               <msContents>
                  <summary>A collection of six poetical works, primarily the <title>Kitāb-i Ḥaydar
                        Bayg</title> (Book of Ḥaydar Bayg) with other shorter works, including the
                        <title>Qiṣṣah-ʾi Mūsh va Gurbah</title> (Story of the Mouse and Cat) and
                        <title>Qiṣṣah-ʾi Sangtarāsh</title> (Story of the Stone Cutter), and the
                        <title>Kitāb-i Ismā‘īl Qurbān</title> (Book of Ismā‘īl Qurbān) together with
                     a ghazal and <title>ta‘ziyat</title> (eulogies). <persName role="scr">Bahman
                        son of Bahman son of Isfandiyar (d. 1788)</persName> copied the volume for
                        <persName role="pat">Sir William Jones</persName>, with whom he lived in
                     Calcutta for 3 years.</summary>
                  <msItem xml:id="Persian_MS_133-item1" n="1">
